                <head>153. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On February 10, 1962, the United States exchanged Colonel <persName
                        corresp="#p_ARI1">Rudolf I. Abel</persName> for <persName corresp="#p_PFG1"
                        >Francis Gary Powers</persName> and Frederick Pryor at the Glienicker
                    Bridge, which linked East and West Berlin. For an account of the exchange by one
                    of the participants, see Donovan, <hi rend="italic">Strangers on a
                    Bridge</hi>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
